modules.description: This module provides functions to query, insert, replace, and merge values within JSON structures using path-based navigation. It operates directly on `Json_repr_browser.Repr.value` types, enabling precise manipulation of JSON documents in a browser-native format. Use cases include extracting nested fields, updating specific nodes, and combining JSON objects efficiently.

This module provides functions to encode OCaml values into and decode them from browser-native JSON representations. It works with OCaml types and the `Json_repr_browser.Repr.value` type, enabling direct interaction with JSON data in web applications. Concrete use cases include serializing OCaml records to JSON for API requests and parsing JSON responses into typed OCaml structures.

This module provides functions to convert between a browser-specific JSON representation and a common abstract view format. It works with JSON values represented as `value` and abstract views of those values. Use it to inspect or manipulate JSON data in a standardized format before converting it back to the browser's native representation.

This module handles JSON data using browser-native representations, providing direct parsing and stringification through `parse`, `stringify`, and related functions. It supports structured manipulation of JSON values via path-based queries and conversions to and from OCaml types. Use it to process JSON in web applications, such as decoding API responses into typed data or building JSON payloads from OCaml structures.
